The numbers are placed on a hexagonal lattice in a clockwise spiral.  
For a cell whose axial coordinates are \((x,y)\) the “ring” (distance from the centre) is  

\[
k=\max\bigl(|x|,|y|,|x+y|\bigr).
\]

For a ring \(k\ge 1\) the first (smallest) number on the ring is  

\[
N_{\text{first}}(k)=N_{\max}(k-1)+1
\]

where  

\[
N_{\max}(k)=1+3k(k+1)
\]

is the largest number on the \(k\)-th ring.  
The first number of the ring is at the axial coordinates \((k,\,-k+1)\).  
From there the walk proceeds along the six sides with the vectors  

\[
(0,1),\;(-1,1),\;(-1,0),\;(0,-1),\;(1,-1),\;(1,0)
\]

(the first side has length \(k-1\); the remaining five sides have length \(k\)).

---

### 1.  Find the coordinates of 2026  

\(2026\) lies in the ring \(k\) satisfying  

\[
1+3(k-1)k < 2026 \le 1+3k(k+1).
\]

\(k=26\) because \(N_{\max}(25)=1951\) and \(N_{\max}(26)=2107\).

The first number of the 26‑th ring is  

\[
N_{\text{first}}(26)=1952,
\qquad\text{at }(26,-25).
\]

The offset of 2026 from the first number is  

\[
2026-1952 = 74 .
\]

The walk along the perimeter gives the following:  

* first side \((0,1)\) – 25 steps,  
* second side \((-1,1)\) – 26 steps,  
* third side \((-1,0)\) – 26 steps, …  

Since \(74>25+26=51\) we are on the third side, having moved \(74-51=23\) steps on it.  
Thus the coordinates are

\[
(0,26) \;+\;(-23,0)=(-23,26).
\]

Hence \(2026\) is at \((-23,26)\).

---

### 2.  The six neighbours

Add the six axial unit‑vectors to \((-23,26)\):

\[
\begin{aligned}
( -22, 26) &\qquad &\text{(east)}\\
( -22, 25) &\qquad &\text{(northeast)}\\
( -23, 25) &\qquad &\text{(northwest)}\\
( -24, 26) &\qquad &\text{(west)}\\
( -24, 27) &\qquad &\text{(south‑west)}\\
( -23, 27) &\qquad &\text{(south‑east)}
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 3.  Convert each coordinate back to its number  

Using the same ring‑formula we obtain:

| coordinate | \(k\) | offset from first of the ring | number |
|---|---|---|---|
| \((-22,26)\) | 26 | \(25+26+22 = 73\) | \(1952+73 = 2025\) |
| \((-22,25)\) | 25 | \(24+25+22 = 71\) | \(1802+71 = 1873\) |
| \((-23,25)\) | 25 | \(24+25+23 = 72\) | \(1802+72 = 1874\) |
| \((-24,26)\) | 26 | \(25+26+24 = 75\) | \(1952+75 = 2027\) |
| \((-24,27)\) | 27 | \(26+27+24 = 77\) | \(2108+77 = 2185\) |
| \((-23,27)\) | 27 | \(26+27+23 = 76\) | \(2108+76 = 2184\) |

---

### 4.  Sum of the six neighbours  

\[
2025+1873+1874+2027+2185+2184 = 12\,168.
\]

\[
\boxed{12\,168}
\]
